ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Would not recommend - I did not learn much from it.
It is a good class but I would not recommend it to another student. I believe there are better resources online to learn this material.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: While I did not learn anything in lecture, i did learn a bit from homeworks, even though that was very hard because the course gave no basis for doing the homeworks whatsoever.
Finally got used to working with github. Made me code different types of problems than I was used to, which was helpful.

This course provided a reinforcement of techniques used in bioinformatics of which I was mostly aware. It allowed me to conceptualize the coding structure of many of the tools. It also gave me greater breadth knowledge of the field and a better context to the fields that surround my research.
This course gave me a broad introduction to bioinformatics which then allows me to pin point which areas of interest I want to further explore.
